                    <span>Up there with Cat's Cradle and Breakfast of Champions, and better than Slaughterhouse Five. This is my personal favorite. Excellent social commentary, intriguing plotline, very funny. Wouldn't suggest it as an introduction to Vonnegut, though it could be worse, for instance, Galapagos would turn lots of readers off (though it is an excellent book as well.), but once you've got a book or two of Vonnegut's under your belt (Cat's Cradle, Bluebeard, or Player Piano are pretty good to start off with) definitely read this.</span>
                  
              
